Rating: 3
I had a leftovers after a crabfest dinner party and this was my first pass at making crab cakes. These were really good and surprisingly easy. Like other cooks suggested, I put them in a 400-degree oven for 30 minutes and broiled them for a couple of minutes at the end to get the crust really crisp, which cut out the time and effort of having to fry them. I only had half a pound of crab meat, so I cut the recipe in half and it still worked. I also didn't have time to prepare the tartar sauce as instructed (salting the cucumbers for half an hour, letting it sit for at least an hour, etc.), so I just tossed everything together, and it was still really good. We each got one cake and it was enough -- they're pretty rich. Pair it with a butter lettuce salad and it makes a great dinner. I'm going to make this again when I have more time and a full pound of crab meat. Enjoy!

