Rating: 4
This is one of my favorite recipes and my stepmother just begged me to make them for her upcoming visit. As to the baking question, here in Delmarva land crab cakes are typically either fried or broiled. I have made these both ways - to broil just lightly spray a baking sheet with oil, place the cakes on the sheet and lightly spray the tops of the cakes with oil. Broil until brown, about 3-4 minutes, on high with the cakes about 4 inches from the flame with the oven door open. I personally don't flip them for fear of breaking them or burning myself or both, but that's just me. They are probably healthier broiled but I think god really intended crab cakes to be fried.

