Rating: 3
Great unadulterated, well-seasoned crab flavor! This is my second year of making these for a big party. I use the 1-lb. cans of Phillips crab from Costco and form the mixture into small (1-1/2") cakes using a small scoop (it helps to pack it rather tightly into the scoop), flatten slightly and refrigerate for a few hours. Then I roll in Panko bread crumbs just before frying. After frying, I place them onto paper towel-lined pans and freeze them individually. Once frozen, they can be placed into Ziploc bags until party time. Place the frozen cakes on a baking sheet lined with parchment and heat in a 375° or 400° oven until hot. We serve it with a chipotle aioli (use a squeeze bottle for fast application). I made a 4X recipe which yielded almost 120 cakes, so a single recipe should yield 25-30 small cakes. Delicious and one of most popular items served at our party!

